{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6328abb4-4aea-480c-8e01-33980c612dd1","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` with the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — re-run tests automatically on file save (hot reload)\n- **`--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~...\"`** — only run tests whose name contains that string\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so you don't need the full namespace. You can also filter by just the method name:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"Name=ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6efc99bd-78dd-458e-b319-a356c6eae0b2","outputTokens":165},"id":"a8f76170-8b7d-4c71-bf18-9a13dbc61678","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:51:14.964Z","parentId":"0367f2f8-de87-4e8a-ae58-7e8cd0c91cdb"}
